hen $s = 7$ cm.',0,'numeric',NULL,5,201,'','solutions/Screenshot_2025-11-21_at_15.32.15.png',0),(260,'','Find the length of the side marked $x$.\r\n\r\n[Right triangle with vertical side x cm, hypotenuse 2 cm, and angle of 60 at bottom right. You will upload the diagram separately.]','3','Expression with square root (e.g., 3 or sqrt(3))','**Step 1:** Identify the triangle components\r\n\r\nThis is a right-angled triangle with:\r\n- Hypotenuse = 2 cm\r\n- Angle at bottom right = 60\r\n- Unknown vertical side (opposite to 60) = $x$ cm\r\n\r\n**Step 2:** Choose the appropriate trigonometric ratio\r\n\r\nWe need to find the opposite side given the hypotenuse, so use sine:\r\n$$\\sin(60) = \\frac{x}{2}$$\r\n\r\n**Step 3:** Solve for $x$\r\n\r\nWe know that $\\sin(60) = \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}$\r\n\r\n$$\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} = \\frac{x}{2}$$\r\n\r\n$$x = 2 \\times \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}$$\r\n\r\n$$x = \\sqrt{3}$$\r\n\r\n**Answer:** $x = \\sqrt{3}$ cm\r\n\r\n**Note:** In a 30-60-90 triangle, if the hypotenuse is 2, the sides are: 1 (opposite 30), $\\sqrt{3}$ (opposite 60), and 2 (hypotenuse).',0,'exact',NULL,5,202,'question_part_images/Screenshot_2025-11-21_at_15.41.33.png','',0),(261,'','Find the length of the side marked $x$.\r\n\r\n[Right triangle with horizontal side (top) 4, angle of 30 at top left, and vertical side (right) x. You will upload the diagram separately.]','43/3','Expression with square root (rationalized form preferred, e.g., 43/3)','**Step 1:** Identify the triangle components\r\n\r\nThis is a right-angled triangle with:\r\n- Horizontal side (adjacent to 30) = 4\r\n- Angle at top left = 30\r\n- Unknown vertical side (opposite to 30) = $x$\r\n\r\n**Step 2:** Choose the appropriate trigonometric ratio\r\n\r\nWe need to find the opposite side given the adjacent side, so use tangent:\r\n$$\\tan(30) = \\frac{x}{4}$$\r\n\r\n**Step 3:** Solve for $x$\r\n\r\nWe know that $\\tan(30) = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}$\r\n\r\n$$\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} = \\frac{x}{4}$$\r\n\r\n$$x = \\frac{4}{\\sqrt{3}}$$\r\n\r\n**Step 4:** Rationalize the denominator\r\n\r\n$$x = \\frac{4}{\\sqrt{3}} \\times \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{\\sqrt{3}} = \\frac{4\\sqrt{3}}{3}$$\r\n\r\n**Answer:** $x = \\frac{4\\sqrt{3}}{3}$ cm',0,'exact',NULL,5,203,'question_part_images/Screenshot_2025-11-21_at_15.42.16.png','',0),(262,'','Find $x$, $y$ and $z$. Give your answers in surd form.\r\n\r\n[Triangle with altitude x creating two right triangles. Left side = 2, left angle = 45, right angle = 30, right side = y, base = z. You will upload the diagram separately.]','x=2, y=22, z=6','Three separate values in surd form (x, y, and z)','**Step 1:** Find $x$ using the left triangle (45 angle)\r\n\r\nIn the left right triangle:\r\n- Hypotenuse = 2\r\n- Angle = 45\r\n- Opposite side (height) = $x$\r\n\r\nUsing sine:\r\n$$\\sin(45) = \\frac{x}{2}$$\r\n\r\n$$\\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{2} = \\frac{x}{2}$$\r\n\r\n$$x = 2 \\times \\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{2} = \\sqrt{2}$$\r\n\r\n**Step 2:** Find $y$ using the right triangle (30 angle)\r\n\r\nIn the right triangle:\r\n- Opposite side = $x = \\sqrt{2}$\r\n- Angle = 30\r\n- Hypotenuse = $y$\r\n\r\nUsing sine:\r\n$$\\sin(30) = \\frac{x}{y}$$\r\n\r\n$$\\frac{1}{2} = \\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{y}$$\r\n\r\n$$y \\times \\frac{1}{2} = \\sqrt{2}$$\r\n\r\n$$y = \\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{\\sin(30)} = \\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{\\frac{1}{2}} = 2\\sqrt{2}$$\r\n\r\n**Step 3:** Find $z$ (the base of the right triangle with 30 angle)\r\n\r\nWe have:\r\n- Opposite side = $\\sqrt{2}$\r\n- Hypotenuse = $2\\sqrt{2}$\r\n- Adjacent side (base) = $z$\r\n\r\nUsing tangent:\r\n$$\\tan(30) = \\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{z}$$\r\n\r\n$$\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} = \\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{z}$$\r\n\r\n$$z = \\sqrt{2} \\times \\sqrt{3} = \\sqrt{6}$$\r\n\r\n**Alternatively, using cosine:**\r\n$$\\cos(30) = \\frac{z}{2\\sqrt{2}}$$\r\n\r\n$$\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} = \\frac{z}{2\\sqrt{2}}$$\r\n\r\n$$z = 2\\sqrt{2} \\times \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} = \\sqrt{2} \\times \\sqrt{3} = \\sqrt{6}$$\r\n\r\n**Answer:** \r\n- $x = \\sqrt{2}$\r\n- $y = 2\\sqrt{2}$\r\n- $z = \\sqrt{6}$',0,'manual',NULL,10,204,'question_part_images/Screenshot_2025-11-21_at_15.42.55.png','',0),(263,'','Find the size of the angle $\\theta$.\r\n\r\n[Right triangle with angle  at top, hypotenuse 10 cm, base 5 cm, right angle at bottom left. You will upload the diagram separately.]','30','Integer value (degrees, without the degree symbol)','**Step 1:** Identify the known sides relative to angle \n\nFor angle $\\theta$ at the top:\n- Opposite side = 5 cm\n- Hypotenuse = 10 cm\n\n**Step 2:** Choose the appropriate inverse trigonometric function\n\nSince we have opposite and hypotenuse, use sine:\n$$\\sin(\\theta) = \\frac{\\text{opposite}}{\\text{hypotenuse}} = \\frac{5}{10} = \\frac{1}{2}$$\n\n**Step 3:** Find the angle\n\n$$\\theta = \\sin^{-1}\\left(\\frac{1}{2}\\right)$$\n\n$$\\theta = 30$$\n\n**Answer:** $\\theta = 30$',0,'numeric',NULL,5,205,'question_part_images/Screenshot_2025-11-21_at_15.56.19.png','',0),(264,'','Find, correct to one decimal place, the value of $\\theta$.\r\n\r\n[Right triangle with angle  at bottom right, horizontal side (top) 2 cm, vertical side (right) 1.41 cm, right angle at top right. You will upload the diagram separately.]','35.2','Decimal to 1 decimal place (degrees, without the degree symbol)','**Step 1:** Identify the known sides relative to angle \r\n\r\nFor angle $\\theta$:\r\n- Opposite side = 1.41 cm\r\n- Adjacent side = 2 cm\r\n\r\n**Step 2:** Choose the appropriate inverse trigonometric function\r\n\r\nSince we have opposite and adjacent, use tangent:\r\n$$\\tan(\\theta) = \\frac{\\text{opposite}}{\\text{adjacent}} = \\frac{1.41}{2}$$\r\n\r\n**Step 3:** Find the angle using a calculator\r\n\r\n$$\\theta = \\tan^{-1}\\left(\\frac{1.41}{2}\\right)$$\r\n\r\n$$\\theta = \\tan^{-1}(0.705)$$\r\n\r\n$$\\theta = 35.2 \\text{ (to 1 decimal place)}$$\r\n\r\n**Answer:** $\\theta = 35.2$',0,'numeric',NULL,5,206,'question_part_images/Screenshot_2025-11-21_at_15.56.40.png','',0),(265,'','Find, correct to two decimal places, the 