INSERT INTO `notes_infobotquery` VALUES (1,'2025-10-09 20:50:08.631571','descriptive-statistics','what is the mean','To calculate the mean (average) of a set of numbers, you need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Add up all the numbers** in the set to get the total sum.\n2. **Count how many numbers** are in the set.\n3. **Divide the total sum by the count** of numbers.\n\nLet\'s go through an example:\n\nSuppose you have the following numbers: \\(4, 6, 10, 12\\).\n\n1. **Sum of all numbers**: \n   \\[\n   4 + 6 + 10 + 12 = 32\n   \\]\n\n2. **Number of numbers**: \n   There are 4 numbers in this set.\n\n3. **Calculate the mean**: \n   \\[\n   \\text{Mean} = \\frac{\\text{Sum of all numbers}}{\\text{Number of numbers}} = \\frac{32}{4} = 8\n   \\]\n\nSo, the mean of the numbers \\(4, 6, 10, 12\\) is \\(8\\).\n\nIf you have a specific set of numbers you want to find the mean for, please provide them, and I can help you calculate it!',0.5846817493438721,'Work out the **mean**, The Mean','ai',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2,'2025-10-31 20:39:48.489560','descriptive-statistics','What is the mean','To find the mean of a set of numbers, you need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Add up all the numbers** in the set to get the sum.\n2. **Count how many numbers** there are in the set.\n3. **Divide the sum by the count** of numbers.\n\nLet\'s go through an example.\n\nSuppose you have the following numbers: 3, 7, 8.\n\n1. **Sum of the numbers**: \n   \\( 3 + 7 + 8 = 18 \\)\n\n2. **Count of the numbers**: \n   There are 3 numbers in total.\n\n3. **Calculate the mean**: \n   \\( \\text{Mean} = \\frac{\\text{Sum of all numbers}}{\\text{Number of numbers}} = \\frac{18}{3} = 6 \\)\n\nSo, the mean of the numbers 3, 7, and 8 is **6**.\n\nIf you have a different set of numbers you\'d like to calculate the mean for, please provide them, and I can help you find the mean!',0.5887420177459717,'Work out the **mean**, The Mean','ai',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(3,'2025-10-31 20:56:23.815965','inferential-stats','what is the mean','To calculate the mean of a set of numbers, you need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Add up all the numbers** in the data set to get the sum.\n2. **Count how many numbers** there are in the data set.\n3. **Divide the sum by the count** of the numbers.\n\nHeres the formula again for clarity:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Mean} = \\frac{\\text{Sum of all numbers}}{\\text{Number of numbers}}\n\\]\n\n### Example Calculation\n\nLet\'s say you have the following set of numbers: \\(4, 6, 10, 12\\).\n\n1. **Sum of all numbers**: \n   \\[\n   4 + 6 + 10 + 12 = 32\n   \\]\n\n2. **Number of numbers**: \n   There are 4 numbers in this set.\n\n3. **Calculate the mean**: \n   \\[\n   \\text{Mean} = \\frac{32}{4} = 8\n   \\]\n\nSo, the mean of the numbers \\(4, 6, 10, 12\\) is \\(8\\).\n\nIf you have a specific set of numbers you\'d like to calculate the mean for, please provide them, and I can help you with that!',0.5846817493438721,'Work out the **mean**, The Mean','ai',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(4,'2025-10-31 21:04:26.419099','descriptive-statistics','What is the mean','To find the mean of a set of numbers, you need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Add up all the numbers** in the data set to get the total sum.\n2. **Count how many numbers** are in the data set.\n3. **Divide the total sum** by the number of values.\n\nLet\'s go through an example to illustrate this process.\n\n### Example:\n\nSuppose we have the following numbers: 4, 10, 6, 8, 4.\n\n1. **Sum of all numbers**:\n   \\[\n   4 + 10 + 6 + 8 + 4 = 32\n   \\]\n\n2. **Number of values**:\n   There are 5 numbers in this set.\n\n3. **Calculate the mean**:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Mean} = \\frac{\\text{Sum of all numbers}}{\\text{Number of numbers}} = \\frac{32}{5} = 6.4\n   \\]\n\nSo, the mean of the numbers 4, 10, 6, 8, and 4 is **6.4**.\n\nIf you have a specific set of numbers you\'d like to calculate the mean for, please provide them, and I can help you find the mean!',0.5588147640228271,'The Mean, Work out the **mean**','ai',NUL