ine Rule, you can use the formula:\n\n\\[\nc^2 = a^2 + b^2 - 2ab \\cos C\n\\]\n\nIn this case:\n- \\( |AB| = 7 \\) (let\'s call this side \\( a \\))\n- \\( |BC| = 5 \\) (let\'s call this side \\( b \\))\n- \\( \\angle ABC = 120^\\circ \\) (let\'s call this angle \\( C \\))\n- \\( |AC| \\) will be the side opposite angle \\( C \\) (let\'s call this side \\( c \\))\n\nNow, substitute the values into the formula:\n\n1. **Identify the sides and angle:**\n   - \\( a = 7 \\)\n   - \\( b = 5 \\)\n   - \\( C = 120^\\circ \\)\n\n2. **Calculate \\( \\cos C \\):**\n   \\[\n   \\cos 120^\\circ = -\\frac{1}{2}\n   \\]\n\n3. **Plug the values into the Cosine Rule:**\n   \\[\n   c^2 = 7^2 + 5^2 - 2 \\cdot 7 \\cdot 5 \\cdot \\left(-\\frac{1}{2}\\right)\n   \\]\n\n4. **Calculate each term:**\n   \\[\n   c^2 = 49 + 25 + 2 \\cdot 7 \\cdot 5 \\cdot \\frac{1}{2}\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   c^2 = 49 + 25 + 35\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   c^2 = 109\n   \\]\n\n5. **Find \\( c \\):**\n   \\[\n   c = \\sqrt{109}\n   \\]\n\nThus, the length of side \\( |AC| \\) is \\( \\sqrt{109} \\), which is approximately \\( 10.44 \\) when calculated. \n\nSo, the final answer is:\n\\[\n|AC| \\approx 10.44\n\\]',0.3292704224586487,'The Mean, The Mean (Average)','ai',NULL,222,'Topic: Trigonometry (1)\nQuestion hint: The Cosine Rule is used to find an unknown side when you have two sides and the included angle. The formula is: $c^2 = a^2 + b^2 - 2ab\\cos C$, where $c$ is the side opposite angle $C$.\nQuestion part ((a)): Find $|AC|$.\r\n\r\n[Triangle ABC with $|AB| = 7$, $|BC| = 5$, and $\\angle ABC = 120$]',283),(21,'2025-11-29 13:56:47.187906','trignometry','What is the cosine formulae','The cosine formulae, commonly known as the Cosine Rule, relate the lengths of the sides of a triangle to the cosine of one of its angles. The formula is given by:\n\n$$\nc^2 = a^2 + b^2 - 2ab\\cos C\n$$\n\nwhere $c$ is the side opposite angle $C$, and $a$ and $b$ are the other two sides.',0.32999250292778015,'The Mean (Average), The Mean','