INSERT INTO `notes_note` VALUES (1,'The Mean','## What is the Mean?\n\nThe **mean** (also called the **average**) is a measure of central tendency that tells you the typical value in a dataset. It represents the \"center\" of your data.\n\n### How to Calculate the Mean\n\n**Formula:**\n$$\n\\text{Mean} = \\frac{\\text{Sum of all values}}{\\text{Number of values}}\n$$\n\nOr using mathematical notation:\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{\\sum x}{n}\n$$\n\nWhere:\n- $\\bar{x}$ (x-bar) = the mean\n- $\\sum x$ = sum of all values\n- $n$ = how many values you have\n\n### Step-by-Step Process\n\n1. **Add** all the numbers together\n2. **Count** how many numbers there are\n3. **Divide** the total by the count\n\n### Worked Example\n\n**Question:** Find the mean of 3, 7, and 8.\n\n**Solution:**\n\n**Step 1:** Add all numbers\n$$\n3 + 7 + 8 = 18\n$$\n\n**Step 2:** Count the numbers\n$$\nn = 3 \\text{ (there are 3 numbers)}\n$$\n\n**Step 3:** Divide sum by count\n$$\n\\text{Mean} = \\frac{18}{3} = 6\n$$\n\n**Answer:** The mean is **6**.\n\n### What Does the Mean Tell You?\n\nThe mean shows the **central value** or **balance point** of your data. In our example, 6 is the typical value - it\'s right in the middle, balancing the smaller values (3) with the larger values (8).\n\n### Quick Check\n The mean should always be between your smallest and largest values  \n In our example: 3 < **6** < 8 \n','mean average what is mean how to calculate mean mean formula central tendency typical value balance point sum divided by count arithmetic mean find the mean calculate average xbar','','[0.04734963923692703, 0.004879942163825035, -0.02863696590065956, 0.02461144886910915, 0.01889202743768692, 0.0025171933230012655, -0.008160638622939587, 0.001544443191960454, 0.015773247927427292, 0.04830619692802429, -0.013989665545523168, 0.027042701840400696, -0.056994933634996414, -0.002745123114436865, 0.06767649948596954, 0.04675178974866867, -0.022897614166140556, 0.02999208867549896, 0.020645717158913612,