20251111_214530.json`\n- `notes_20251111_214530.json`\n\nKeep these files! They\'re your safety net if something goes wrong.\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Workflow:\n\n### Daily Development:\n1. Work on questions locally at http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/\n2. Test thoroughly\n3. Run `./sync_to_production.sh` when ready\n4. Reload web app on PythonAnywhere\n\n### Quick Fixes:\n- Small typos/fixes can be done directly on production admin\n- For multiple changes, always work locally first\n\n### Before Major Changes:\n```bash\n# Backup production first\n./sync_from_production.sh\n# Now work locally\n# Then push when ready\n./sync_to_production.sh\n```\n\n---\n\n## Troubleshooting:\n\n**\"Permission denied\"**\n```bash\nchmod +x sync_to_production.sh sync_from_production.sh\n```\n\n**\"Connection refused\"**\n- Check your PythonAnywhere password hasn\'t changed\n- Update password in the scripts if needed\n\n**\"Conflicts detected\"**\n- The scripts use `loaddata` which will update existing records\n- It matches by primary keys\n- New items will be added, existing ones updated\n\n**\"My changes disappeared!\"**\n- Check your backup files (`questions_*.json`)\n- You can manually load them: `python manage.py loaddata questions_20251111_214530.json`\n\n---\n\n## Security Note:\n\n **Remember to change your PythonAnywhere password!**\n\nThe scripts currently have your password hardcoded (`Newtcsp@8899`). After changing your password, update it in:\n- `sync_to_production.sh` (line 15)\n- `sync_from_production.sh` (line 15)\n\nChange `PA_PASSWORD=\"Newtcsp@8899\"` to your new password.\n\n---\n\n## Need Help?\n\nIf you encounter issues:\n1. Check the error message\n2. Look at the backup files created\n3. Check PythonAnywhere error logs\n4. You can always manually export/import using Django\'s dumpdata/loaddata commands','# Database Sync Guide  I\'ve created two scripts to help you sync your databases between local and production.  ## Scripts Created:  ### 1. `sync_to_production.sh` - 